<br>
When your hobby becomes a chore, that is a clear sign that it shouldn't be your hobby anymore.  After quitting my guild of 1.5 years, all the motivation to log on is gone. I have thought about joining another one, but then it just seems to be the same thing over again. <br>
<br>
Then I think about how much money I am saving by just zoning out playing EQ rather than go clubbing or buying other games.  Then I break down and log on for a weekend xp grindfest.  Its better to be bored and have some results of yer boredom validated on a little yellow/blue bar then just by a spot of drool on yer shirt. =P <p><font size="-1">Chibibroli Beguiler, 60 Dark Elf Phantasmist -<b></b>-<br>
